According to Elf spec it is always 4 bytes.  It seems to work OK for 64-bit:

$ adb pull /system/framework/arm64/boot.oat
[100%] /system/framework/arm64/boot.oat

$ readelf -n boot.oat
Displaying notes found at file offset 0x000003c0 with length 0x00000024:
  Owner                 Data size	Description
  GNU                  0x00000014	NT_GNU_BUILD_ID (unique build ID bitstring)
    Build ID: 57f2052d4afe52af4bd6c707d942bd0671c465de



name and size have multiple of 4 length here.  Added a static assert to document / enforce better.

